.IX Title "GETCRL 8"
.TH GETCRL 8 "2005-08-17" "perl v5.8.3" " "
.SH "NAME"
getcrl.sh \- CRL downloader and installer
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBgetcrl.sh\fR [\fB\-s\fR] \s-1URL\s0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBgetcrl.sh\fR downloads a \s-1CRL\s0 from the \fI\s-1URL\s0\fR, verifies it against root
certificates directory and installs it into a \s-1CRL\s0 directory for use of
\&\fBOpenSSL\fR\-based applications. Both direcotries use the \fBOpenSSL\fR directory
structure (see \fIx509\fR\|(1), \fIcrl\fR\|(1)).
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-s\fR" 4
.IX Item "-s"
Log output messages to standard error, as well as the system log. unless
this option is set no output is generated which is suitable for \fIcron\fR\|(8)
jobs.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.IX Header "RETURN VALUE"
\&\fBgetcrl.sh\fR returns one of the following exit values:
.IP "\fB0\fR Success." 4
.IX Item "0 Success."
.PD 0
.IP "\fB1\fR Error in options and/or arguments" 4
.IX Item "1 Error in options and/or arguments"
.IP "\fB2\fR Error creating temporary working directory" 4
.IX Item "2 Error creating temporary working directory"
.IP "\fB3\fR Error downloading the \s-1CRL\s0" 4
.IX Item "3 Error downloading the CRL"
.IP "\fB4\fR Error parsing the \s-1CRL\s0" 4
.IX Item "4 Error parsing the CRL"
.IP "\fB5\fR The \s-1CRL\s0 could not be verified" 4
.IX Item "5 The CRL could not be verified"
.IP "\fB6\fR The \s-1CRL\s0 could not be installed" 4
.IX Item "6 The CRL could not be installed"
.PD
